Ecom Agroindustrial Corp., a
supplier of commodity raw materials, hired banks to arrange a
$300 million  credit line  to refinance a facility maturing in
October.  ABN Amro Bank and Credit Agricole SA are arranging the 364-
day revolving credit that can be extended by another year, the
banks said in a statement today.  The credit line will replace the Pully, Switzerland-based
companyâ€™s $530 million facility signed last year, according to
